-- City Leads at Halftime Against QPR; On Course for League Title
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-05-13T14:50:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/city-leads-at-halftime-against-qpr-on-course-for-league-title.html
Manchester City leads Queens Park
Rangers 1-0 at halftime in today’s final round of Premier League
matches, keeping the club on course for a first English soccer
championship in 44 years.  City was tied on points with 19-time champion  Manchester
United  before today, but had a superior goal difference. United
leads 1-0 at Sunderland.  Pablo Zabaleta scored for City after 39 minutes, with Wayne
Rooney getting United’s goal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  